"a.十恶不赦的 【英】 adj. 十恶不赦的(outrageo usly wicked or evil; abominable) 【考】 反义词：commendable (值得表扬的) 【例】 Even the police were shocked by the heinous crime. adj. 十恶不赦的 = abominable = reprehensible 【读】黑nous(多): 做什么事都特别黑－十恶不赦的 【反】commendable(adj 值得表扬的); admirable(adj 令人倾佩的) 【记】音：hein 狠 + ou 恶 + s 死；它太恶，狠死它了 heinous (adj.)  late 14c., from Old French hainos ""inconvenient, awkward; hateful, unpleasant; odious"" (Modern French haineux), from haine ""hatred,"" from hair ""to hate,"" from Frankish, from Proto-Germanic *hatjan, related to *haton (see hate (v.)). Related: Heinously; heinousness."
